questions: Who is the current CEO of Google?
What is the Capital of India
Is Sundar Pichai the CEO of Google?

data.response_text:
The current CEO of Google is Sundar Pichai. 

- **Full Name**: Pichai Sundararajan
- **Date of Birth**: June 10, 1972
- **Nationality**: Indian American
- **Position**: Chief Executive Officer (CEO) of Alphabet Inc. and its subsidiary Google.
- **Leadership Focus**: Under his leadership, Google has been focused on developing innovative products and services, particularly in the realm of artificial intelligence and information accessibility.

For more information, you can visit his [Wikipedia page](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sundar_Pichai) or his [Google Blog profile](https://blog.google/authors/sundar-pichai/).

The capital of India is New Delhi. 

- New Delhi is part of the National Capital Territory of Delhi (NCT).
- It serves as the seat of all three branches of the Government of India.
- Geographically, New Delhi is located in the north-central part of India, to the west of the Yamuna River.
- The city was established as the capital of India in 1911, marking a significant shift from Calcutta (now Kolkata).
- For more information, you can visit the following links:
  - [New Delhi - Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Delhi)
  - [Delhi - Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Delhi)
  - [What is the capital of India? - USA Today](https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2023/05/24/what-is-the-capital-of-india/70195720007/)
  - [New Delhi - Britannica](https://www.britannica.com/place/New-Delhi)

Yes, Sundar Pichai is the CEO of Google. 

- Sundar Pichai was appointed as the CEO of Google on August 10, 2015, following his role as chief product officer under then-CEO Larry Page.
- He officially took on the CEO position on October 24, 2015, coinciding with the formation of Alphabet Inc., which became the parent company of Google.
- In addition to being the CEO of Google, he also serves as the CEO of Alphabet Inc., the parent company of Google.

For more information, you can visit his profile on Wikipedia: [Sundar Pichai - Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sundar_Pichai).
